  "texts": [
    "Similarly, on the CNN/DailyMail dataset, SSH attains a ROUGE-1 score of 44.89, which is marginally lower than AFLoRA (44.95) by 0.06 points, but it outperforms LaMDA (44.16) by 0.73 points.",
    "In terms of ROUGE-2, SSH achieves 21.75, trailing AFLoRA (21.87) by 0.12 points but exceeding LaMDA (21.17) by 0.58 points.",
    "Additionally, SSH attains a ROUGE-L score of 42.13, which is 0.12 points lower than AFLoRA but significantly higher than LaMDA by 1.65 points.",
    "Overall, SSH consistently demonstrates strong performance while requiring significantly fewer trainable parameters (0.21M) compared to AFLoRA (5.27M) and LaMDA (0.85M).",
    "Models and Dataset."
  ],
